getCurrentFoundBeacons

public static void getCurrentFoundBeacons(java.util.List<Beacon> outerList)
Gets the list of currently detected beacons. The external list is filled with a snapshot of the internal beacon list, this way the list instantiation and control remains outside of the SDK. One last thing to comment is that this method is an alias for the method BeaconManager#getSnapshotBeaconsList(List).

Example of usage: 

 List<Beacon> myActivityInternalList = new ArrayList<Beacon>();
 MobiquityManager.getCurrentFoundBeacons( myActivityInternalList );

Parameters:
outerList - The list of beacons to fill.
